cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with audio classification, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
- cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with speech processing, it does deal with natural language in the form of audio labels. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper deals with supervised machine learning and proposes a new method for improving classification performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a method for improving the performance of a system (i.e., a classification model) by detecting and relabelling certain instances. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with natural language in the form of audio labels and proposes a method for improving classification performance.
